#. type: Plain text
#: ./modules/retail/pages/snippets/trust_gpg.adoc:4
msgid ""
"By default, some operating systems do not trust the GPG key for the "
"{productname} client tools.  The clients can be successfully bootstrapped "
"without the GPG key being trusted.  However, you will not be able to install "
"new client tool packages or update them until the keys are trusted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: ./modules/retail/pages/snippets/trust_gpg.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Trusting GPG Keys on Clients"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ./modules/retail/pages/snippets/trust_gpg.adoc:11
msgid ""
"On the {productname} Server, at the command prompt, check the contents of "
"the [path]``/srv/www/htdocs/pub/`` directory.  This directory contains all "
"available public keys.  Take a note of the key that applies to the client "
"you are registering."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ./modules/retail/pages/snippets/trust_gpg.adoc:13
msgid ""
"Open the relevant bootstrap script, locate the [systemitem]``ORG_GPG_KEY=`` "
"parameter and add the required key.  For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: ./modules/retail/pages/snippets/trust_gpg.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "uyuni-gpg-pubkey-0d20833e.key\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ./modules/retail/pages/snippets/trust_gpg.adoc:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "  You do not need to delete any previously stored keys.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ./modules/retail/pages/snippets/trust_gpg.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are bootstrapping clients from the {productname} {webui}, you will "
"need to use a Salt state to trust the key.\n"
"Create the Salt state and assign it to the organization.\n"
"You can then use an activation key and configuration channels to deploy the "
"key to the clients.\n"
msgstr ""
